  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/snowflake/d21e39f3-b66e-45d0-a6ae-e4899e7e8581/application",
    "company": "Snowflake",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "f2c9f75833cc7fb5",
    "department": "Sales",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nThere is only one Data Cloud. Snowflake’s founders started from scratch and designed a data platform built for the cloud that is effective, affordable, and accessible to all data users. But it didn’t stop there. They engineered Snowflake to power the Data Cloud, where thousands of organisations unlock the value of their data with near-unlimited scale, concurrency, and performance. This is our vision: a world with endless insights to tackle the challenges and opportunities of today and reveal the possibilities of tomorrow.\n\nSnowflake continues to grow its Partner Program, helping partners onboard and thrive in the Snowflake Partner Network (SPN). As the Global Partner Program Lead, you will play a crucial role in overseeing the performance of Partner Program Specialists, ensuring program objectives are met and that partners have an outstanding experience as they advance within the SPN. This is a high-impact role requiring a strong focus on execution, cross-functional and cross-region collaboration, and leadership.\n\nThe Global Partner Program Lead is responsible for ensuring Partner Program Specialists follow standard operating procedures to support partners through key activities, including onboarding and advancing in the program, training and certification, and program renewal. In this role, you will be accountable for ensuring that the team delivers measurable results in alignment with program goals and driving program activities directly with partners.\n\nRequirements:\n\n - Advanced English Speaker. Fluent in verbal and written English.\n\n - Additional language capabilities (Plus - Japanese or Mandarin)\n\n - Experience managing people and building teams\n\n - Must have Customer or Partner service experience\n\n - 3 to 5 years of Job Experience in the following roles: Partner Programs, Partner/Customer Support, Partner/Sales Operations, Project Management, Sales, Teaching/Training, Customer Success Management\n\n - Exposure or previous experience in channel programs (Plus)\n\n - Ability to drive a high volume of projects while maintaining a high level of organization and attention to detail\n\n - Strong time management, organization, and prioritization skills are needed. (must)\n\n - Ability to develop and deliver messages and presentations to executive audiences\n\n - Demonstrated ability to influence cross-functional teams and work in a leadership role\n\n - Strong problem-solving skills with a focus on process improvement and partner experience enhancement\n\n - Experience working in a fast-paced, dynamic environment with a focus on partner success and program management\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n - Oversee the results and performance of Global Partner Program Specialists to ensure program objectives and partner milestones are met\n\n - Act as a point of escalation for any partner-related issues and provide guidance on resolutions\n\n - Collaborate with cross-functional teams, including sales, enablement, and support, to drive program success\n\n - Ensure consistent delivery of best practices, program requirements, and onboarding processes to partners through the team\n\n - Monitor team performance metrics and ensure alignment with SPN program objectives.\n\n - Identify gaps and opportunities within the partner experience, propose solutions, and lead initiatives to enhance program effectiveness\n\n - Provide coaching and mentorship to Partner Program Specialists, helping them deliver high-quality support to partners\n\n - Lead strategic initiatives to scale the SPN program and enhance partner satisfaction\n\n - Continuously assess the effectiveness of the onboarding and enablement processes, making recommendations for improvement\n\n - Work in collaboration with the other Program Acceleration Centers to ensure consistency and standardisation\n\n - Interact with partners via verbal and written communication; present key information and resources using prescribed presentation materials and superior presentation skills\n\n - Guide partners through the SPN programs and their associated tiers\n\n - Drive program onboarding engagement, ensuring that the partner has an outstanding experience\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
